\section{System Architecture}
% ==============================================================

\subsection{Architecture Overview}
The system is organized into five layers. The \textbf{Presentation Layer} (Django HTML templates with Bootstrap~5.3) handles question display, answer input, and timer visualization with fullscreen enforcement via the browser Fullscreen API. The \textbf{Controller Layer} (Django views) coordinates the test lifecycle, implements synchronous rule-based difficulty fallback, and spawns asynchronous agent threads. The \textbf{AI/Agent Pipeline Layer} executes the CrewAI multi-agent pipeline (SOLMA$\rightarrow$SOLPA$\rightarrow$SOLTA) in background daemon threads communicating with Gemini~2.5 Flash. The \textbf{Question Generation Layer} invokes Google Gemini to generate MCQs on-the-fly at specified difficulty levels, enforcing a strict JSON schema (\texttt{id}, \texttt{question}, \texttt{options[4]}, \texttt{correct\_answer}, \texttt{explanation}). The \textbf{Data Layer} provides durable MySQL-backed storage via three Django models: \texttt{StudentTestResult}, \texttt{QuestionPerformance}, and \texttt{AdaptiveLearningHistory}.

\subsection{APOT Model Adaptation}
The original APOT model~\cite{outay2024} follows a cyclic Assess, Predict, Oversee, and Transit process managed by LSAA, SOLMA, SOLPA, and SOLTA agents. Fig.~\ref{fig:apot_model} illustrates the original APOT cyclic model and its agent roles. In our adaptation:

\begin{itemize}
    \item The \textbf{Assess} stage maps to the MCQ Evaluator Agent, implementing \textbf{SOLMA} (Stage of Learning Monitoring Agent) by monitoring answer correctness.
    \item The \textbf{Predict} stage maps to the Difficulty Predictor Agent, implementing \textbf{SOLPA} (Stage of Learning Prediction Agent) by classifying current question difficulty.
    \item The \textbf{Oversee} and \textbf{Transit} stages jointly map to the Adaptive MCQ Overseer Agent, implementing \textbf{SOLTA} (Stage of Learning Transition Agent) by synthesizing analyses and determining difficulty transitions.
    \item The \textbf{LSAA} (Learning Style Assessment Agent) function is embodied by domain-aware question generation across three cognitive domains (Reasoning, Aptitude, Verbal Ability) and multi-domain competency tracking on the analytics dashboard.
\end{itemize}

