\subsection{Agent Role Separation and APOT Integrity}
The three-agent design enforces separation of concerns mirroring the APOT model~\cite{outay2024}. SOLMA handles only factual comparison, ensuring correctness determination is isolated from difficulty reasoning. SOLPA applies psychometric heuristics to the current question without considering adaptation goals. SOLTA alone integrates correctness, predicted difficulty, and adaptive rules for transition recommendations. This staged design prevents conflation and makes each agent's reasoning independently auditable.

