\section{Implementation}
% ==============================================================

The system is implemented as a full-stack web application using Django~4.2 (Python) with MySQL as the database backend. The multi-agent pipeline is orchestrated through CrewAI~0.28.0, with each agent powered by Google Gemini~2.5 Flash via both the CrewAI LLM wrapper (for agent reasoning, temperature~0.7) and the \texttt{google-generativeai}~0.3.0 SDK (for MCQ generation). The frontend uses Bootstrap~5.3 with vanilla JavaScript for the interactive test interface, including Fullscreen API integration and \texttt{navigator.sendBeacon} for tab-closure handling.

The test session supports 20~questions per assessment with a 20-minute timer. Session state---including the dynamically generated question list, current index, answer history, skipped indices, and difficulty progression---is maintained in Django's built-in session framework. Per-question timing is captured client-side with millisecond precision and transmitted as whole seconds. Topics are constrained via a normalized vocabulary with alias mapping (e.g., ``quant'' and ``quantitative aptitude'' both resolve to \textit{aptitude}).

The analytics dashboard computes CI scores, domain-level accuracy breakdowns, weekly performance trends, and competency badges (Dedicated Learner, Perfect Score, Most Improved, domain-specific mastery badges). A leaderboard ranks users by average score and assigns competency bands.

